        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 19 at 8:20PM PDT by NWS Spokane WA</headline>
        <description>At 819 PM PDT, trained weather spotters reported a strong
thunderstorm near Dover, or near Sandpoint, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Pea size hail.

SOURCE...Trained weather spotters.

IMPACT...Torrential rainfall will lead to ponding of water and
localized flooding on area roadways.

Locations impacted include...
Dover, Sandpoint, and Ponderay.

This includes the following highways...
U.S. Highway 95 in Idaho between mile markers 464 and 475.
U.S. Highway 2 in Idaho between mile markers 17 and 28.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
